# React Native UI Structure

- Keep screens as thin orchestration layers. Move reusable UI into components, reusable stateful behavior into hooks, and API or storage work into services/helpers.
- Use typed props for components and hooks. Prefer explicit return types for exported helpers and services.
- Keep component files focused: one primary component per file, with local styles and small private helpers only when they support that component.
- Introduce or extend a shared theme/tokens file before repeating colors, spacing, radii, font sizes, or sizing values across multiple files.
- Use tokens for shared UI decisions, for example `space.md`, `radius.lg`, `fontSize.xl`, or `color.background`, instead of scattering hardcoded values.
- Build components so they are testable without an emulator: pass dependencies through props or small services when practical, and keep side effects outside presentation components.
